<ul class="project-title-and-text">

    <li class="project-title">
        Bartram's Garden Rebrand
    </li>

    <li class="project-type">
        Brand Identity
    </li>

    <li class="project-tools">
        Illustrator, Photoshop, Figma, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, GSAP
    </li>

    <!-- <li class="project-objective-title">
        Objective
    </li>

    <li class="project-body-text">
        To create a new brand identity for Bartram's Garden.
    </li> -->

    <li class="project-objective-title">
        About
    </li>

    <li class="project-body-text">
        Bartram's Garden is the oldest surviving botanical garden in North America. My goal with the new design was to
        bring Bartram's apiculture into equal standing visually. The hexagon became the unifying form because it repeats
        itself throughout Bartram's different avenues. While it's the geometry of a honeycomb, it's also how petals
        arrange and how seeds pack.
    </li>

    <!-- <li class="project-process-title">
        Process
    </li>

    <li class="project-body-text">
        Since Bartram's Garden is involved in agriculture, horticulture, and apiculture, those three elements
        were taken into consideration when designing a new logo. The hexagonal leaf, flower, and honeycomb cell 
        motifs are used repeatedly throughout the brand. Items such as flyers, merchandise, and environmental
        branding are included to remind viewers of Bartram's Garden's main areas of operation. The logo animation
        was made with code (HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and GSAP), while the logo and other elements were developed in
        Illustrator.
    </li> -->
</ul>

